One Last Thing

You’ve probably noticed something else:

Most symbolic systems end up with 12 or 13 core archetypes.

That happens because once you combine these root metaphors, you get roughly that many stable roles.

Which is why you see:
	•	12 Olympians
	•	12 tribes
	•	12 zodiac signs
	•	12 knights
	•	12 disciples

It’s not mystical.

It’s combinatorial stability in narrative systems.

